abstract: GRAND RAPIDS, Mich., March 30.--John E. Sullivan, the professional baseball player, committed suicide here last night by taking morphine. He received injuries by falling from a balcony two years ago, which rendered him deaf and mentally unsound. He had been melancholy and dissipated since the accident. He leaves a widow in destitute circumstances.
